Developer publishes or updates the application for the Service Provider:
  1. uStore (or manually the user accessing the uStore) can invoke the Testing Server's API in order to run one or more tests. run_test(...) API (the name could be renamed in the future) let the actor specify the set of Targets to be tested. The Testing Server produces some kind of result (here expressed as Result obj) necessary in order to add the certificate the application.
  2. uStore (or manually the user accessing the uStore) can run the tests by specifying the Target. The Result obj is necessary to add the certificate the application

1. Developer writes code or models applications

  3. AAL Studio can exploit inner tools in order to run the tests or interact with the Testing Server in order to lunch the tests
  4. AAL Studio sends a report to the developer by means of (e.g) alert on the test Eclipse perspective or on the web-based user interface.
